WEBVTT

00:03.086 --> 00:04.880
Okay, here's the thing

00:03.086 --> 00:04.880
about my family:

00:04.922 --> 00:06.966
we don't go on a lot of outings

00:04.922 --> 00:06.966
together, but when we do,

00:07.007 --> 00:09.134
there's a little tradition

00:07.007 --> 00:09.134
we always end up observing.

00:09.176 --> 00:10.552
When you say lifetime ban,

00:10.594 --> 00:12.137
I mean, whose lifetime

00:10.594 --> 00:12.137
are you talking about?

00:12.179 --> 00:13.889
REESE:

00:12.179 --> 00:13.889
Ow! Mom, let my feet

00:13.931 --> 00:15.140
touch the ground.

00:15.182 --> 00:16.934
Don't you ever ask me

00:15.182 --> 00:16.934
for anything ever again.

00:16.976 --> 00:18.727
I should've just

00:16.976 --> 00:18.727
given birth to chimps.

00:18.769 --> 00:21.104
Then at least I know

00:18.769 --> 00:21.104
to expect this kind of behavior.

00:21.146 --> 00:22.272
Ow!

00:22.314 --> 00:24.065
Believe it or not,

00:22.314 --> 00:24.065
I actually envy Dewey.

00:24.107 --> 00:26.694
He got to stay home and play

00:24.107 --> 00:26.694
with the babysitter.

00:26.735 --> 00:29.571
And then the ambulance came,

00:26.735 --> 00:29.571
but there was this balloon.

00:29.613 --> 00:30.948
And then I was chasing it,

00:30.990 --> 00:32.449
and then I didn't know

00:30.990 --> 00:32.449
where I was.

00:32.491 --> 00:34.075
And then I chased a bag,

00:34.117 --> 00:35.995
and then I really didn't know

00:34.117 --> 00:35.995
where I was.

00:36.036 --> 00:37.120
And then I saw you,

00:37.162 --> 00:39.080
and I thought

00:37.162 --> 00:39.080
maybe you could help me

00:39.122 --> 00:41.917
because you helped that other

00:39.122 --> 00:41.917
girl-- the one in the movie.

00:41.959 --> 00:44.461
So if you could just

00:41.959 --> 00:44.461
come to life and help me,

00:44.503 --> 00:46.505
I'd really appreciate it.

00:49.758 --> 00:51.927
DEWEY:

00:49.758 --> 00:51.927
Thanks anyway.

