02:55.258 --> 02:58.053
"Sugar, corn syrup and gelatin."

02:58.095 --> 03:01.723
How can something so

02:58.095 --> 03:01.723
simple be so delicious?

03:01.765 --> 03:03.433
That stuff's nasty, Francis.

03:03.475 --> 03:05.602
To the unsophisticated

03:03.475 --> 03:05.602
palate, yes,

03:05.644 --> 03:09.064
but to me, the Candy Quack

03:05.644 --> 03:09.064
is nature's perfect food.

03:09.106 --> 03:11.692
I'll bet I could eat

03:09.106 --> 03:11.692
a hundred of them.

03:11.733 --> 03:14.862
No way. All that marshmallow

03:11.733 --> 03:14.862
would expand in your stomach.

03:14.903 --> 03:16.237
You wouldn't get past 50.

03:16.279 --> 03:18.239
Okay, there's where

03:16.279 --> 03:18.239
you're wrong, Joe.

03:18.281 --> 03:20.241
See, the marshmallow

03:18.281 --> 03:20.241
wouldn't expand.

03:20.283 --> 03:21.242
It would dissolve.

03:21.284 --> 03:22.870
I'd never get full.

03:22.911 --> 03:23.871
In fact, I don't...

03:23.912 --> 03:26.081
Will you just shut up!

03:26.123 --> 03:27.624
I have sat back

03:27.666 --> 03:31.128
and said nothing

03:27.666 --> 03:31.128
while you've gone on and on

03:31.170 --> 03:33.964
about how you can eat

03:31.170 --> 03:33.964
a hundred of this

03:34.006 --> 03:36.257
and lift a hundred of that.

03:36.299 --> 03:39.053
The Quacks would expand.

03:39.094 --> 03:41.096
You're an idiot

03:39.094 --> 03:41.096
if you think different.

03:41.138 --> 03:43.891
Okay, let me tell

03:41.138 --> 03:43.891
you something.

03:43.932 --> 03:47.061
If I say I can eat

03:43.932 --> 03:47.061
a hundred Quacks,

03:47.102 --> 03:49.646
you can take that as

03:47.102 --> 03:49.646
a bona fide guarantee.

03:49.688 --> 03:52.357
And there's no need to resort

03:49.688 --> 03:52.357
to personal attacks,

03:52.399 --> 03:54.151
because I'd hate to raise

03:54.193 --> 03:58.238
the whole issue of you

03:54.193 --> 03:58.238
wearing boxers in the shower.

04:07.164 --> 04:09.083
That was so cool.

04:09.124 --> 04:11.168
Did you see that truck

04:09.124 --> 04:11.168
jackknife and flip over

04:11.210 --> 04:12.544
and that wheel fly

04:11.210 --> 04:12.544
through the air?

04:12.586 --> 04:14.295
An explosion

04:12.586 --> 04:14.295
would've been nice,

04:14.337 --> 04:15.923
but you can't

04:14.337 --> 04:15.923
have everything.

04:15.964 --> 04:17.298
Yeah, Reese,

04:15.964 --> 04:17.298
this is great.

04:17.340 --> 04:19.300
Now we're stuck

04:17.340 --> 04:19.300
here for hours

04:19.342 --> 04:21.302
with no food and no

04:19.342 --> 04:21.302
air-conditioning.

04:21.344 --> 04:23.013
I guess it could be worse.

04:23.055 --> 04:25.640
I could be the guy

04:23.055 --> 04:25.640
in the silver Toyota.

04:27.559 --> 04:29.394
Why can't you just

04:27.559 --> 04:29.394
open one lane?

04:29.436 --> 04:31.563
Lady, we have to wait

04:29.436 --> 04:31.563
for the crane to get here

04:31.605 --> 04:34.315
before we can even think of

04:31.605 --> 04:34.315
opening this road to traffic.

04:34.357 --> 04:36.235
Yeah, but if you just moved a

04:34.357 --> 04:36.235
couple of those police cars,

04:36.276 --> 04:37.819
there'd be enough room to

04:36.276 --> 04:37.819
just pass on the shoulder.

04:37.861 --> 04:39.613
I mean, this is

04:37.861 --> 04:39.613
just plain stupid.

04:39.654 --> 04:42.323
Ma'am, don't call

04:39.654 --> 04:42.323
a police officer stupid.

04:42.365 --> 04:44.325
What, that's a law now?

04:44.367 --> 04:45.744
Look, my freshman year,

04:45.786 --> 04:47.996
I ate seven pounds of grapes

04:45.786 --> 04:47.996
in one sitting.

04:48.038 --> 04:50.582
I think I know what my body

04:48.038 --> 04:50.582
is capable of.

04:50.624 --> 04:53.168
We're not talking

04:50.624 --> 04:53.168
about grapes, Francis.

04:53.210 --> 04:55.336
We're talking

04:53.210 --> 04:55.336
about pure sucrose.

04:55.378 --> 04:56.588
The human body simply

04:56.630 --> 04:59.549
cannot absorb the sugar

04:56.630 --> 04:59.549
in 100 Quacks.

04:59.591 --> 05:00.634
CADETS:

04:59.591 --> 05:00.634
Yeah!

05:00.675 --> 05:02.219
Hey, in extreme cases,

05:02.261 --> 05:04.846
the human pancreas has

05:02.261 --> 05:04.846
been known to increase

05:04.888 --> 05:06.265
its insulin production

05:04.888 --> 05:06.265
by up to 60%.

05:06.306 --> 05:07.724
CADETS:

05:06.306 --> 05:07.724
Yeah!

05:07.766 --> 05:09.434
Listen, your pancreas can

05:07.766 --> 05:09.434
produce enough insulin

05:09.476 --> 05:10.769
to fill a swimming pool.

05:10.811 --> 05:12.353
That doesn't mean squat

05:12.395 --> 05:14.231
if your adrenal gland

05:12.395 --> 05:14.231
can't distribute it

05:14.273 --> 05:15.816
into your bloodstream

05:14.273 --> 05:15.816
fast enough!

05:15.857 --> 05:17.151
CADETS:

05:15.857 --> 05:17.151
Yeah!

05:17.192 --> 05:18.944
(cadets arguing)

05:18.986 --> 05:20.279
Gentlemen, gentlemen!

05:20.320 --> 05:22.322
This argument is pointless.

05:32.582 --> 05:34.293
One.

05:37.420 --> 05:39.422
Look, look at that--

05:37.420 --> 05:39.422
they're just standing around.

05:39.464 --> 05:41.424
Yeah, 500 cars full of people

05:39.464 --> 05:41.424
who actually have

05:41.466 --> 05:43.468
someplace to go, and they're

05:41.466 --> 05:43.468
just standing there talking.

05:43.510 --> 05:44.845
What is there to discuss?!

05:44.886 --> 05:47.388
Hey! Let me clear

05:44.886 --> 05:47.388
something up for you!

05:47.430 --> 05:48.807
This is a car wreck!

05:48.849 --> 05:52.393
You're a road crew.

05:48.849 --> 05:52.393
Do your job!

05:52.435 --> 05:55.438
Are you even listening

05:52.435 --> 05:55.438
to me?

05:55.480 --> 05:57.274
That could

05:55.480 --> 05:57.274
have been me.

05:57.316 --> 05:59.400
Yeah, well, Hal,

05:57.316 --> 05:59.400
it could've been all of us.

05:59.442 --> 06:01.320
Nope! No, that

05:59.442 --> 06:01.320
car was sliced

06:01.360 --> 06:03.113
right through

06:01.360 --> 06:03.113
the driver's seat.

06:03.155 --> 06:06.491
You and the boys would've

06:03.155 --> 06:06.491
walked away without a scratch.

06:06.533 --> 06:08.493
This totally sucks.

06:08.535 --> 06:10.411
It's like an oven out here.

06:10.453 --> 06:13.414
What is the point of wandering

06:10.453 --> 06:13.414
aimlessly through traffic?

06:13.456 --> 06:15.667
So we can find cool stuff

06:13.456 --> 06:15.667
like this.

06:15.709 --> 06:16.710
(chuckles)

06:16.751 --> 06:18.253
Smells like gasoline.

06:18.295 --> 06:20.047
Reese, can't we just

06:18.295 --> 06:20.047
go back to the car?

06:20.088 --> 06:21.089
My feet are killing...

06:21.131 --> 06:22.423
Ice cream man!

06:22.465 --> 06:24.425
(kids clamoring)

06:24.467 --> 06:26.427
Go away!

06:26.469 --> 06:29.430
There is no ice cream

06:26.469 --> 06:29.430
in the truck!

06:29.472 --> 06:30.682
He's lying!

06:30.724 --> 06:33.143
There's tons of ice cream

06:30.724 --> 06:33.143
in there!

06:33.185 --> 06:36.479
The ice cream in the truck

06:33.185 --> 06:36.479
is not for sale!

06:36.521 --> 06:38.439
It is against the law

06:38.481 --> 06:41.526
for me to sell ice cream

06:38.481 --> 06:41.526
in the middle of traffic!

06:41.568 --> 06:43.237
This is just wrong!

06:43.278 --> 06:45.446
You could make money

06:43.278 --> 06:45.446
and please children.

06:45.488 --> 06:46.907
This is a senseless act.

06:46.948 --> 06:49.450
You are evil--

06:46.948 --> 06:49.450
pure evil!

06:49.492 --> 06:51.452
Well, if you kids

06:49.492 --> 06:51.452
are not willing

06:51.494 --> 06:53.372
to discuss this sensibly...

06:56.875 --> 06:58.252
You son of a...!

06:58.293 --> 06:59.753
Look, there's nothing

06:58.293 --> 06:59.753
you can do.

06:59.794 --> 07:00.837
Yes, there is.

07:00.879 --> 07:02.297
I can... I can...

07:02.339 --> 07:03.715
(yelling)

07:05.508 --> 07:06.634
(groaning)

07:06.676 --> 07:09.470
And the Nobel

07:06.676 --> 07:09.470
Prize goes to...

07:09.512 --> 07:12.515
Hey, you're talking

07:09.512 --> 07:12.515
about my brother.

07:12.557 --> 07:14.059
Good one.

07:14.101 --> 07:15.769
I'm Jessica-- gray Volvo.

07:15.810 --> 07:17.478
Malcolm-- crappy minivan.

07:17.520 --> 07:19.480
Do you want to go check

07:17.520 --> 07:19.480
out the crash site?

07:19.522 --> 07:22.359
Sure. You know, my dad

07:19.522 --> 07:22.359
practically caused it.

07:22.401 --> 07:23.568
Wow.

07:25.195 --> 07:26.487
What time is it now?

07:26.529 --> 07:27.572
It's still 4:00.

07:27.614 --> 07:29.157
You have to wait

07:27.614 --> 07:29.157
at least a minute

07:29.199 --> 07:30.533
for the time

07:29.199 --> 07:30.533
to change, dear.

07:30.575 --> 07:32.202
What time is it in China?

07:32.244 --> 07:34.495
Well, sweetie,

07:34.537 --> 07:35.997
I think they're

07:34.537 --> 07:35.997
a good 20 hour...

07:36.039 --> 07:37.582
Do you speak Chinese?

07:37.624 --> 07:39.334
Well, no. I...

07:39.376 --> 07:40.501
Is Chinatown in China?

07:40.543 --> 07:42.296
Honey, if you want

07:42.337 --> 07:44.923
an answer to a question,

07:42.337 --> 07:44.923
you have to first wait...

07:44.965 --> 07:46.507
What does this toe do?

07:46.549 --> 07:49.552
You know what? I need to

07:46.549 --> 07:49.552
buy a pack of cigarettes--

07:49.594 --> 07:52.931
for the first time

07:49.594 --> 07:52.931
in 20 years.

07:58.937 --> 08:00.772
DEWEY:

07:58.937 --> 08:00.772
Grape juice, please.

08:03.442 --> 08:04.359
(glass shatters)

08:04.401 --> 08:06.486
(people screaming)

08:09.030 --> 08:11.408
WOMAN:

08:09.030 --> 08:11.408
He's getting away!

08:16.621 --> 08:18.832
(tires screeching)

08:23.670 --> 08:25.255
(whoops)

08:29.759 --> 08:31.594
Hello.

08:40.479 --> 08:42.397
Think about it, Lois.

08:42.439 --> 08:45.400
I stopped to tie my shoe

08:42.439 --> 08:45.400
in the parking lot.

08:45.442 --> 08:46.734
If I hadn't done that,

08:46.776 --> 08:49.237
we would've been

08:46.776 --> 08:49.237
on the road 20 seconds sooner.

08:49.279 --> 08:51.990
I would've been 200 yards

08:49.279 --> 08:51.990
ahead of where I was,

08:52.032 --> 08:54.575
and then I would've

08:52.032 --> 08:54.575
been the silver Toyota.

08:54.617 --> 08:56.577
And if you hadn't

08:54.617 --> 08:56.577
rented  Body Heat,

08:56.619 --> 08:57.787
we never would

08:56.619 --> 08:57.787
have had Dewey.

08:57.829 --> 08:59.080
It's all an intricate

08:57.829 --> 08:59.080
tapestry, Hal.

08:59.122 --> 09:00.581
OPERATOR:

08:59.122 --> 09:00.581
Ma'am?

09:00.623 --> 09:03.502
Yes. Hello... D-Did you

09:00.623 --> 09:03.502
ask your supervisor?

09:03.543 --> 09:05.003
Yes, and this phone is for

09:05.045 --> 09:06.963
emergency roadside assistance

09:05.045 --> 09:06.963
only, ma'am.

09:07.005 --> 09:08.798
I can't connect you

09:07.005 --> 09:08.798
to a private line.

09:08.840 --> 09:11.592
Look, I have got to get

09:08.840 --> 09:11.592
through to my babysit...

09:11.634 --> 09:14.388
Look. J-Just let me talk

09:11.634 --> 09:14.388
to the supervisor.

09:14.429 --> 09:15.680
One moment, ma'am.

09:15.722 --> 09:18.766
(deep voice):

09:15.722 --> 09:18.766
Hello. This is the supervisor.

09:18.808 --> 09:20.185
No, it isn't.

09:20.227 --> 09:22.020
You're just disguising

09:20.227 --> 09:22.020
your voice.

09:22.062 --> 09:24.647
No, I'm not.

09:22.062 --> 09:24.647
I'm really the supervisor.

09:24.689 --> 09:26.274
You can't do this!

09:26.316 --> 09:28.318
Ma'am, I'm about to be replaced

09:26.316 --> 09:28.318
by a machine.

09:28.360 --> 09:30.695
I can do whatever

09:28.360 --> 09:30.695
I damn well please.

09:30.737 --> 09:33.781
H-Hey! Where do you think

09:30.737 --> 09:33.781
you're going, young lady?

09:33.823 --> 09:36.326
It's okay. My dad's an

09:33.823 --> 09:36.326
investigator for the D.O.T.

09:36.368 --> 09:38.453
Oh, there he is.

09:36.368 --> 09:38.453
Hi, Daddy!

09:41.664 --> 09:43.458
Okay.

09:44.667 --> 09:47.628
Whoa. Your dad's

09:44.667 --> 09:47.628
a crash investigator?

09:47.670 --> 09:49.464
Here's a little

09:47.670 --> 09:49.464
secret, Malcolm:

09:49.506 --> 09:52.426
whenever you want something,

09:49.506 --> 09:52.426
everybody's your dad.

09:52.467 --> 09:53.676
Hi, Daddy!

09:57.722 --> 10:02.810
Okay, she's cute, she's smart,

09:57.722 --> 10:02.810
and she even lies to cops.

10:02.852 --> 10:05.230
I may be in over my head here.

10:05.272 --> 10:08.525
CADETS:

10:05.272 --> 10:08.525
Forty-six!

10:08.567 --> 10:11.361
Forty-seven!

10:11.403 --> 10:12.946
Forty-eight!

10:36.719 --> 10:38.638
(ice cream truck music playing)

10:44.436 --> 10:46.687
And when you're constantly

10:44.436 --> 10:46.687
moving from town to town,

10:46.729 --> 10:48.731
it's really hard

10:46.729 --> 10:48.731
to make friends.

10:48.773 --> 10:50.900
So, yeah, I acted

10:48.773 --> 10:50.900
out, I guess.

10:50.942 --> 10:52.777
But who wouldn't

10:50.942 --> 10:52.777
in my situation?

